<section class="py-5 mt-5" style="background-color: #fef9e9;">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Page Title, Problem Description, and Symptoms -->
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-xl-6 text-center mx-auto">
        <!-- Title in one line -->
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold mb-4" style="line-height: 1.2; color: #260d5e;">
          How to Stop Severe Bleeding Before Medical Help Arrives
        </h1>
        <!-- Brief problem description -->
        <p class="lead text-muted">
          Rapid blood loss is life-threatening. Immediate action can reduce the risk of shock.
        </p>
        <!-- Short symptoms section in red -->
        <p class="fs-5" style="color: red;">
          <strong>Symptoms:</strong> Profuse bleeding, weakness, and rapid heartbeat.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Main Content: Do's and What Not To Do -->
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <!-- Left Column: Guidelines -->
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3">Immediate Steps (Do's):</h3>
        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Apply Direct Pressure:</strong> Use a clean cloth or bandage to press firmly on the wound.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Elevate the Injured Area:</strong> Raise the wounded limb above the heart if possible.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Secure the Pressure:</strong> Bind the cloth in place to maintain steady pressure.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Call Emergency Services:</strong> Dial your local emergency number immediately.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Do not remove objects embedded in the wound.</li>
          <li>Avoid applying a tourniquet unless you are trained.</li>
          <li>Do not apply ice directly to the wound.</li>
          <li>Avoid delaying professional help.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted mt-3">
          <em>Note:</em> This guide is for emergency use only and does not replace professional medical treatment.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Right Column: Image Placeholder -->
